      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAYBE NEXT WEEK (4) scored by 2.5 lengths last time (17.85) in a NG over 320m at this track. Makes strong appeal on best. STEPHEN WITHERAP (7) is a well performed dog and winner of 18 races who was in the minor money last time out at this track (18.04). Form here at the trip sound including 18 wins. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Can feature again. BUSY MAN (1) is a well performed sprinter ideally suited at the shorter trips. Kept coming to fill the minor placings over 320m at this track (18.18) in a Free For All. Form here at the trip excellent including 14 wins. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Overdue and is among the main hopes. ELECTRIC ASSENT (8) collected a minor prize last start and ran time in the process - must be considered.",
